OL,3,CReduction in VAT rates in next week's
OL,4,Cbudget 'vital' for their survival
OL,6,FAlready it's having an impact on
OL,7,Fborder businesses - those leading the
OL,8,Fcharge for change believe long term
OL,9,Fthe treasury won't lose out.
OL,11,FColin Neill from Hospitality Ulster
OL,12,Fsays: "This would stabilize the
OL,13,Findustry. 18 months or so, and you
OL,14,Fstart to see that pass through to the
OL,15,Fcustomer.
OL,17,F"All of our research again says the
OL,18,FChancellor would be break-even within
OL,19,Ftwo to three years and then be a plus,
OL,20,Fbecause they get more VAT from more
OL,21,Fbeing sold.
